        <abstract> 
<p>Is certain he never had Morren’s paper from JOW or heard of it before JOW’s note; will write to <hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi> about it [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">3252</hi>].</p>  
<p>Thanks for the two <hi rend="italic">Sphinx</hi> moths; unfortunately the pollen-masses do not belong to orchids but to <hi rend="italic">Asclepias</hi>.</p>  
<p>Asks whether R. B. Todd’s <hi rend="italic">Cyclopedia of Anatomy and Physiology</hi> [1835–59] has an article on fertilisation of orchids.</p> 
        </abstract>
